The deadly 'queen bee' of the Borg Collective and one of humanity's greatest nightmares. Her background is unknown, but her goal is clear: the complete assimilation of all organic life.
The adopted human sister of Spock, Burnham serves aboard the U.S.S. Discovery. Fiercely intelligent, driven, with a moral drive that occasionally brings her into conflict with her superior officers.

An old school Klingon warrior. Despite his appreciation for Earth culture, he foresees the end of the Klingon Empire if the Federation continues to advance and is willing to do anything to prevent this occurring.
A true polymath, Pavel Chekov has served in multiple roles including security, navigation and tactics. He excels in all of them, while always maintaining his trademark good cheer.
A selfless doctor whose past accomplishments include serving as Head of Starfleet Medical. A consummate team player always willing to put the needs of her colleagues first.
Medical officer aboard the U.S.S. Discovery. A kind-hearted man who always fights for his patients and is willing to stand up to authority on their behalf.
Commander Data is the first android ever to serve in Starfleet. Despite his super-human strength, agility and intelligence, he pursues an endless quest to become more human.
The Doctor is an Emergency Medical Hologram (EMH) Mark I, a walking, talking comependium of medical expertise. The Doctor continues to learn and evolve as he serves aboard the U.S.S. Voyager.
An unknown but a powerful entity that inhabits the Nexus.
An unknown but extremely powerful entity that inhabits the Nexus.
Dukat is a 'gul', a high-ranking commander in the Cardassian armada. His practiced charm hides an insidious, power-hungry mind one willing to sell out anyone or anything for power.

A survivor of the Romulan supernova event, Elnor was evacuated to Vashti by Admiral Picard. As an adult, he became a rare, male adjunct of the Qowat Milat, an order of warrior nuns. Their training has left him almost unmatched in martial combat.
A seemingly mild-mannered Cardassian tailor, Garak is a former member of the Obsidian Order, the intelligence agency of his people's' government. An able assassin, saboteur and consummate spymaster.
The Borg equivalent of a worker-bee. Quiet, efficient and usually focused on repairing any damage nearby. Most ignore intruders as they're seen as too irrelevant to bother with.
While the Borg don't have doctors, they do have drones built specifically to repair disabled units and keep the Collective active. Somewhere between butchers and mechanics.
A form of Drone adapted to enhance their technical processing power. They take an active role when planets or ships are assimilated; helping harvest the captives.
A Borg Drone specifically designed for heavy combat. They're usually equipped with durable shields and a range of weapons appropriate to the encounter and environment.  A truly terrifying foe.

The Cardassian Empire is famed throughout the Quadrant as a brutal place, one where absolute loyalty to the state is demanded and only the strongest are allowed to rise.  Such a person is the Cardassian Commander.
The Cardassian counterpart to Starfleet's engineering crews. The majority are female, as most males lack the technical acumen required to keep ships and equipment running smoothly.
Cardassian doctors are just as ruthless as the rest of their military, eager to increase their knowledge at any cost. Rumors of torture and reprogramming are more than just Federation propaganda.
A member of the Cardassian Science Ministry, an organization tasked with ensuring that any of the more dangerous military inventions are... palatable... to the general population.
The rank and file of the Cardassian war machine. Each is raised from the cradle to believe in the superiority of their Empire and their right to dominate the Alpha Quadrant.

To become the Commander of a Starfleet vessel is an honor, reserved for the brightest and best. Each is trained in tactics, negotiations, philosophy and all manner of studies that help promote the Federation philosophy as they expand throughout the Quadrant.
Starfleet engineers are trained to think on their feet, prepared for any eventuality, and able to adapt any technology, alien or otherwise, to meet the needs of their ship.

Starfleet's medical personnel provide essential support to every ship and colony to which they're assigned. All are extensively trained in xenobiology to serve the wide range of species that make up the Federation.
Starfleet scientists embody the core tenets of Starfleet's mission: curiosity, exploration, discovery, and the quest to increase knowledge of the universe beyond.
The "red tunics" provide the backbone of all Starfleet expeditions. Dedicated and resourceful, rumors of their high mortality rate are (mostly) overstated.

A leader used to a crew renowned throughout the quadrant as some of the finest warriors in existence.  Each flies into battle knowing that their ancestors are watching and determined to make them proud.

If you need a ship repaired fast and with brutal efficiency, the Klingon Engineer is the crew member you need. If you're lucky they might throw in a few blood stained banners or smoldering vents for a bit of local 'flavor'.
A medic although one who's a bit more... rudimentary than their Starfleet equivalents. Each was born into a culture where death in battle was considered an honor, after all...

While Klingons have a reputation for being warriors, they've been responsible for some of the greatest technological advances seen in the Quadrant. Such works are built by their scientists who are a welcome addition to any crew.
What one would expect from a Klingon soldier.  Each is powerful, loyal and brave; devoted to the defense of their people.

A blade of the Empire, forged in its fires and finally given command of one of their Warbirds. All are skilled in battle but also in survival: each knows that at any moment they could be betrayed and lose their position of power.
Romulan engineers are not as safety-conscious as their Federation counterparts. Efficiency and lethality are their guiding principles, all in service to the greater Empire.
Part of the Romulan medical corp. Each is extremely well trained but, unlike their Federation counterparts tend to specialize primarily on their own species.
Romulan scientists are all too willing to push the boundaries of scientific ethics. They've been responsible for some of the quadrants' greatest inventions... and some of its worse horrors.

Warriors charged with eliminating threats to the Romulan Empire. They are adept at physical confrontations but also are well versed at dealing with spies and other forms of subterfuge that dominate the empire's politics.
Despite being born blind, Geordi has worked his way up from helmsman to Chief Engineer of the U.S.S. Enterprise. His VISOR allows him to "see" things beyond the limit of human sight.

The former leader of the Terran Empire, now a Section 31 operative. Cold and ruthless, she'll sacrifice millions for the sake of her ambitions. Her only weakness is her fondness for her adopted daughter, Michael Burnham.

An alien species first encountered by Captain Kirk and the Enterprise. Their reptilian physiology grants incredible strength and endurance: the Gorn are widely considered one of the most physically powerful of the known races.
The famous captain of the U.S.S. Voyager. Her tenacity and brilliance helped save her ragtag crew as they ventured deeper into uncharted space than any previous Starfleet vessel.

A 20th century Augment dictator woken from cryosleep by the crew of the U.S.S. Enterprise centuries later. Gifted by a eugenics program that made him smarter, faster and stronger than regular men... but far more arrogant.

Captain James Tiberius Kirk is arguably the most legendary captain in Starfleet history. His quick thinking, boldness and charisma have saved the lives of his crew - and saved the Federation - countless times.

A nightmare created when Captain Picard was assimilated by the Borg. Possessing all of the Captain's tactical genius and knowledge of Starfleet protocols, Locutus retained only a shred of his humanity.

One of Starfleet's best, a decent, hardworking captain loved by his crew.  Or... so he'd like you to believe.  Lorca is from the Mirror-Universe and, like that place, a black hearted reflection of the man he replaced. Malicious, scheming and hungry for power, no one should take their eyes off him. Ever.
A famed Klingon who acted as the chief commander of their forces during the 24th century. Considered by military historians to be an excellent tactician with a rare ability to bond with his troops.
Chief Medical Officer of the U.S.S. Enterprise under Captain Kirk. A gruff man famous for his sardonic sense of humour, his broad set of skills and, more than anything else, his inherent humanity.
A Bajoran ally of the Federation, working on the Deep Space Nine station after its liberation from Cardassian forces. A determined patriot devoted to her people, Kira never accepts defeat.
Assimilated by the Borg as a child, Seven is one of the few survivors of the Borg's brutality. Her remaining cybernatic enhancements make as lethal in combat as she is brilliant in strategy.
A mysterious shapeshifter rescued by Bajorans, Odo rose to become the security officer of the Deep Space Nine station. Gruff, solitary and possessed of a firm sense of justice.
Arguably one of the greatest doctors in Starfleet history. Phlox is a Denobulan, an alien race eager to learn more about their new human neighbours. A xenobiologist without peer.

Widely considered one of the greatest captains in Starfleet history. Renowned as a tactician, thinker and diplomat, Captain Picard strives to uphold the ideals of the Federation, no matter the challenges he faces.
Former captain of the U.S.S. Enterprise. A kind, decent man doomed to suffer a terribly injury that leaves him voiceless and immobile.

A Ferengi trader, bartender and occasional criminal  (though he'd loudly protest that the latter were only a long series of 'misunderstandings' between himself and any number of local authorities). It's rumored he has a heart of latinum, but keeps it locked safely in a bank vault with the rest of his wealth.
The quintessential First Officer: unquestionably loyal, unfailingly brave, and always willing to put his crew ahead of himself. A rare officer who was content to serve rather than seek command.

Saru is a Kelpian, an alien species born with a unique ability to sense danger. The first of his kind to join Starfleet, his dedication and skill led him to become First Officer on the U.S.S. Discovery.
Chief Engineer of the U.S.S. Enterprise under Captain Kirk and famous for (in no particular order) his genius, his love of whiskey, and his proud Celtic heritage.
A half-Romulan, half-Human hybrid. She has little but scorn for mankind, preferring the cool, sharp intellect and fierce passions of her father's people. Treachery is her forte.

The Federation commander of station Deep Space Nine during the Dominion War. A proud leader and philosophical general, he is as comfortable ruminating on religion as he is creating revolutionary battle tactics.

Growing up, Soji believed she was a normal woman, working as an anthropologist in Romulan space. This was a lie.  She was an android, built from the same systems that once created Data.  Her life so far has been a lie, created by others.  Her future, though, remains in her hands.
Easily the most famed Vulcan in Starfleet history, Commander Spock is renowned for his logic, his thoughtfulness, and his firm friendship with Enterprise crewmates Captain Kirk and Dr. McCoy.
A science officer, or more accurately an 'astromycologist' on board the U.S.S. Discovery. A genius, he helped design the revolutionary spore drive. A brusque but kind hearted man.
The fearless helmsman of the U.S.S. Enterprise, tasked with piloting her on her epic five year mission. As Spock once said, despite his calm demeanor Sulu is, at heart, a swashbuckler.

An android, one of a series built using Soong technology. Sutra is hostile to humans, seeing them as little more than outsiders who wish to destroy her and her kind.  She seeks an alliance with a race of god-like synthetics who's whispers have been heard across the Quadrant.

An ensign aboard the U.S.S. Discovery. A theoretical engineer by training, Tilly is in turns shy, ambitious and always incredibly warm hearted. Those who push past her awkward exterior will have a friend for life.
A legendary Romulan commander, famed among his people for his cunning... and among his enemies for his treachery.

Less an individual and more a klingon legend come to life; a ceremonial warrior who acts as champion and uniter of the 24 great houses in case of war or coming catastrophe. The Torchbearer always wore striking golden armor.

A half-Klingon, half-Human, former Maquis engineer. Pressed into service aboard the U.S.S. Voyager, she often struggles with her warring halves as she solves complex engineering problems with out-of-the-box solutions.

A Vulcan officer assigned to the U.S.S. Enterprise NX-01 during the historic mission that introduced humankind to the stars. She is calm and thoughtful, with a core of steel that has served her shipmates well.

A half betazoid empath who served on the U.S.S.Enterprise under Captain Picard. A warm, friendly woman whose ability to understand her shipmates and psychological training makes her a perfect counselor.

The third in command of the U.S.S. Voyager and that vessel's head of security. While deadly in a fight, his true strength lies in his Vulcan upbringing; he is logical, thoughtful and always has a plan for every eventuality.
Communications officer aboard the U.S.S. Enterprise under Captain Kirk. Her fluency in alien languages and calm under pressure make her an invaluable member of the crew.

In another era, Worf would have been an enemy of the Starfleet. Instead, this proud Klingon rose to become one of its greatest officers: a warrior, a diplomat and an indispensable member of the Enterprise crew.

Thanks for responding to my distress call!
I don't know where I am or how I got here, but the locals aren't very friendly!
Destroy the intruder!
Youre the U.S.S. Artemis? I dont know that name, but I'm glad you're here!
Somethings preventing me from beaming out. Sabotaging the ships warp core should solve the problem!
Can you send over any crew to help me?
Good to see-- Wait, a Klingon in a Starfleet uniform?!
You would mock a fellow officer?
Im just glad youre on my side!
One minute Im on the Discovery investigating a strange energy ribbon, the next Im fighting alongside a Klingon.
I hope I didnt inhale some of Stamets spores
These names are unknown to me. But this energy ribbon you speak of I encountered one too before finding myself here!
We can discuss it later. Lets get to Engineering and shut down their warp core!
Artemis, were ready to beam out of here!
The Cardassians are attempting to block our signals. We must hold them off until we can safely transport!
Cardassian technology is no more advanced than Starfleets. We should be able to disable their warp core easily.
Whats a Cardassian?
Cardassians!
You... You're not real! Youre ghosts, like the others!
Are all you Cardassians this paranoid? Stand down and well get you medical assistance.
We wont fall for any more of your Federation tricks. Fire at will!
Im hit...!
Hold still and let me patch you up!
I am Gul Dukat, commander of the Cardassian forces stationed here. We will not fall prey to any more deception!
I declare this base and its personnel to be property of the Cardassian Union. You specters will not stand in my way!
Surrender your weapons or be destroyed!
Klingons do NOT surrender!
As you wish. Soldiers, weapons ready!
What the devil are these Cardassians going on about? Ghosts?
We must reach the Federation base.
Were almost there. Odd, Im still not reading any life signs...
Ive located supplies. It seems they were left behind by the Cardassians.
Why, thats <color=#fff15c>Protomatter!</color> We can use that to upgrade or unlock new Skills.
I'm picking up life signs around the base. Energy readings show traces of an attack. Could be the Cardassians.
Any sign of Starfleet crew out there?
Not yet. Atmospheric ionization could be blocking a precise reading from our tricorders.
We should prepare for battle. The Cardassians will NOT show mercy.
These bodies Their wounds dont look like they were caused by those Cardassian weapons.
Commander Burnham of the U.S.S. Discovery hailing Federation outpost, please respond! I repeat, this is Commander Burnham...
We must assume the worst. The Cardassians may have penetrated the facilitys defenses.
Lets regroup on the Artemis and plan our next move.
Finally a friendly face! Can you tell us whats happened here?
Hostile entities detected. Engaging countermeasures.
They are hardly friendly, Doctor!
These must be what the Cardassians were talking about. Their ghosts.
Its the damnedest thing. One moment theyre here, the next they vanish.
Could they be some form of holographic projection?
Hopefully well find answers deeper inside the base.
Escalating threat level. Engaging intruders.
Tricorder scans indicate that these are definitely holograms, but I've never seen ones so sophisticated.
Holodecks have yet to be invented in your time, obviously.
These holograms appear to be some form of automated defense system.
They must be generated from somewhere deeper inside the base.
Security breach in sector A-23. Searching for countermeasures... Stand by.
Response found. Experience indicates a 96.32% chance of successful removal of intruders.
I recognize her. It is Captain Janeway of the U.S.S. Voyager!
Let us hope this imitation is not as formidable as the Captain herself.
Do you think Janeway was involved in this?
Impossible. Theres something else at work here. Something nefarious
We should regroup back on the ship. Burnham to Artemis, three to beam up.
Unknown personnel detected. Error. Memory circuit compromised.
Damned thing is going haywire. Looks like well have to find our own way in.
I suggest we cut through the door. It is the most direct approach.
Or I can override the doors security protocols. A more cautious approach might be better
The <color=#fff15c>Choices</color> you make during missions can affect their outcomes, unlocking <color=#fff15c>new rewards or alternate paths!</color>
Qapla! Were through, Captain. The Cardassians will not be prepared for us!
Ive managed to override the door controls.
Ive also reactivated the bases defense system. We should be somewhat protected if theres any danger ahead.
I have located a storage chest, but I am having difficulty opening it...  This mechanism is most aggravating.
Dont look at me. Im a doctor, not a locksmith.
Let me take a look. I have a knack for this kind of thing
Im accessing the complexs database. This is a research facility working on something named Project Talos.
That would explain the ghosts. These scientists must have been inspired by Talosian illusions. Ive had first-hand experience with them. All too real.
As in Talos IV? But travel to that planets forbidden by Starfleet.
Blame Spock.
You know that aggravating Vulcan too?
Its a long story.
Chief scientists personal log. Weve made a breakthrough with Project Talos.
Exposing the central logic circuits to various threat scenarios has increased its combat effectiveness by 72.3%.
Talos, how are we doing today?
All systems are operating within 99.2% of normal parameters.
My staff has expressed ethical concerns about subjecting such an advanced artificial intelligence to repeated traumatic combat scenarios.
I have to remind them that its still a computer, not a human being, even considering our recent modifications. End recording.
Deploying defensive countermeasures. Shields to full power.
Theyve got a mobile force field emitter protecting them!
Thank you for opening the doors. We lay claim to this base for the Cardassian Union!
Stop firing at us, you idiots! We're flesh and blood, same as you!
I suggest conversing them AFTER we incapacitate them, Doctor.
If this is a Starfleet program, it will be programmed to obey our orders.
Computer, this is Lieutenant Worf of the U.S.S. Enterprise. Cease all aggressive activity at once!
Command not accepted.  Primary protocol is protecting the central Core. Talos must survive.
Continuing simulation N32-B. Experience indicates chance of Starfleet intruder survival at 0.007%.
All intruders must be terminated. Talos must survive.
Stop attacking us! Were Starfleet officers! Even the Klingon!
Thank you, Doctor. I think.
We should return to the Artemis before attempting to disable the core. It will be heavily protected.
We are near the central core. How should we proceed?
Looks like the left path leads to the medical bay. We might find some more bio-mimetic gel there.
Ive found another terminal. The encryption is extremely secure I dont know if Ill be able to hack it!
Gathering medical supplies would be wise. I believe we have not fought our last battle here
A wise decision! We must know more about our enemy if we are to defeat it in combat.
Choose which path to follow. Youll be able to try different paths when you replay missions.
Ive found another terminal. The files have been partially deleted, but... this facility was run by Section 31!
Who the devil are they?
Section 31 is a clandestine group within Starfleet. Theyre prepared to do anything to protect the Federation.
This base was testing a new form of tactical computer.
They discovered an experimental processor, capable of granting the device a more... human response.
Hrm. That sounds suspiciously like an "emotion chip". It can have... unpredicatable results.
They were trying to use it to predict the behavior of biological life forms, creating a machine that knows how we think...
... then using that against us.
But what about the researchers that were here? Where are they now?
Ive found another personnel log. Stand by...
Chief scientists personal log. Thanks to the new processor, were making extraordinary progress!
Weve programmed Talos to create more realistic and unpredictable holograms.
But there have been concerns that the sheer amount of energy required has begun to destabilize some of the secondary systems.
There is no cause for alarm, chief scientist.
Such disruptions are well within the range of acceptable stress parameters. Our work together will proceed as planned.
... Thank you, Talos. End log.
Sounds like this Talos has a mind of its own...
Were almost at the core. Be careful!
I am more than ready to end this.
Stand down, Talos!
Hostile entities encountered. Upgrading threat level to epsilon-orange. Generating defensive measures.
You just had to go and irritate the damn thing...
Hostile entities have accessed Core. Threat level at maximum. Searching files for counter. Searching... Searching...
Designation: Tactician required. Expert leadership required. Searching Starfleet files, sub-category: Commander.
I think it's trying to find someone strong enough to defeat us...
Result: William T. Riker, First Officer of the U.S.S. Enterprise.
Riker is a trusted friend. But we must remember that these are only holograms!
Error. System compromised. Purging excess energy. Defenses will reactivate in 572 seconds.
The core is unprotected. We must strike now!
This machine is responsible for the death of everyone involved in its creation. Its too dangerous. Weve got to destroy it!
Perhaps
But on MY Enterprise, Commander Data was an android with an intelligence matching that of Talos, and I was honored to call him my friend.
Talos seeks to preserve itself. Is that not a sign of sentience?
First a Klingon officer, now a robot? Whats gotten into Starfleet in the future?
This energy seems to be corrupting the system. If we purge it, we can restart Talos and give him a second chance.
Ive destroyed the programs core. Talos is inoperative. Forever.
Ive purged the excess energy from the system and triggered a restart of Taloss core systems.
Keep your fingers crossed...
Ive found another personal log...
Emergency log. Talos is no longer following our commands.
A mysterious power surge in the core has Talos is stuck in a feedback loop.
It thinks our threat response scenarios are real. Its trying to purge the base using the EDH programs!
Ive sent out a distress signal, but I dont know how much longer we can--
--Transmission terminated--
This blasted machine killed everyone! It cant distinguish between a simulation and reality!
Operation parameters uncertain. Extreme measures taken to protect central core. Talos must survive.
Computer, what is the status of Project Talos?
There are no records of Project Talos in the Starfleet database.
Finally, a machine that will listen to us! Its about time.
The system is coming back online. Here goes nothing...
System online. Identifying Starfleet personnel. Welcome to Talos Base, Doctor McCoy.
At least its learned some manners.
Well disable the distress call. Youll be left alone for a long time, Talos.
System diagnostic in progress. Searching for new directives... Thank you for your assistance.
Im reading a powerful energy source inside the machine
Let me see... Ah! Theres some sort of device inside the housing!
Perhaps this is the experimental processor they mentioned?
I dont know. Ive never seen anything like it before.
Intriguing. The energy pouring out of it appears similar to the ribbon in space that trapped us here in the Nexus.
Youre right, man. Let's bring it back to the ship. With any luck it might tell us more about this damn dimension!
Have you found the human whose signal we intercepted?
No. The commander wont be pleased. Wait.. Over there! Federation dogs!
The commander will be happier when we bring her prisoners of war! Weapons ready!
Romulans! If they are searching for Captain Kirk, he is in grave danger.
First time Ive ever seen one. Theres been no contact with them since the war ended a century ago.
Count yourself lucky. My Enterprise was the first to see them since then. I wish theyd kept their distance.
My tricorder shows a storm blowing in. Wed better move quickly.
How do you know Spock, anyway? Were you students together at the Vulcan science academy?
We're siblings, Doctor. And before you ask, I was adopted.
Hmphh. You do seem a little green-blooded
Stop! This is as far as you go.
What have you done with Captain Kirk?
The captain is in very good hands. But it is a pity youll never see him again.
Well... sounds like he's alive, at least.
But for how long, in Romulan hands? We must find him!
Spock to Artemis away team. I must commend your efforts. Youve handled the situation with near Vulcan precision.
Our scans indicate another Romulan encampment within several kilometers of your present position.
It is likely they are holding Captain Kirk nearby.
Im detecting a Starfleet beacon from within that shuttle...
No sign of Jim. He must still be out there. We should check the shuttlecrafts logs.
We should proceed with caution and scan the area. There may be more Romulans cloaked nearby.
Logs show Captain Kirk was the pilot.
No sign of where he went from here, but they indicate were weapons fired before the shuttle landed.
There shall be no sign of you, either!
Im detecting more Romulans approaching. Get ready to defend yourselves!
Ah, Doctor McCoy. A pleasure to hear your voice. And you as well, Michael, after all this time.
Wait...  you two know each other? How?
A story for another time. Unfortunately, Captain Kirk is missing. The shuttle he was aboard has vanished.
Long range scans detect a Federation distress signal on Trigon VII, the planet you are orbiting... It could be from the captain.
Your assistance in locating him would be appreciated. Enterprise out.
Was that really him? Was it Spock?
No His resonance signature is consistent with the Nexus. The real Spock is still out there, somewhere
Then he is no more than a phantom. Still, we do not know if the Kirk he described is real or not. We should investigate.
You fools run blindly toward your deaths!
Empty words from a cowards mouth! To battle!
Well need to subdue these Romulans before they warn Sela of our approach!
You again? Im surprised you were able to sneak up on our position.
How positively Romulan of you!
You wont get away this! Hand over Captain Kirk!
Should I be threatened by a doctor?
Your self-righteousness bores me. Lets get this over with.
Wait! Hold your fire!
Your mother would have fought until the end!
My mother was a fool who died running away.

To where? What are you devils planning?
He's of no value to us. To others, however, hes a tantalizing prize
You WILL tell us Captain Kirks location.
Very well. Theres no way youre going to save him. Hes being held by Romulan High Command as a prisoner of war...
The empire is planning to exchange him for an alliance with the Gorn.
I would hurry if I were you. The Gorn arent known for their hospitality Hah!
A Romulan encampment, hastily abandoned. We should search it for clues to Kirks location.
That device over there looks like a comms unit. Ill try to hack its logs
This datapad belonged to a Romulan Centurion
It appears the Romulans are transporting Captain Kirk southeast, to a Romulan transport site.
The Romulans have purged the files, but Ive been able to restore fragments of the log.
Looks like they were in contact with an unidentified vessel.
No doubt cloaked conveniently out of sight
Ive found Selas position as well! If we hurry, we might be able to reach Captain Kirk before they leave the planet!
They were certainly in a hurry to get out of here. They left valuable supplies behind.
Sub-commander, what is your status? Respond!
Sela! You bring dishonor to the name of Tasha Yar.
I'm working for the good of my people. I havent betrayed them, like you have.
You fool! Youre trapped in this Nexus just like we are!
Nexus? What nonsense is this?
She doesnt know What if shes part of this place?
Enough of this. Where is Captain Kirk?
If you value your lives, you will forget your captain!
Farewell. I cant imagine well meet again.
What is that?!
You wouldnt have met one yet, but Jim Kirk did. Theyre called the Gorn.
Drazz'tak norshgrrz!
It seems the universal translator is having difficulty with the Gorn language...
He is challenging us to battle! Prepare yourselves!
Worf, you speak Gorn?
Not expressly, but as a Klingon warrior, one has a knack for reading between the lines.
Commander Tomalak has ordered you eliminated, Federation pests.
Do you think this is over?
My warbird waits in orbit. I'll return and blast you to atoms!
Dramatic fellow. He's right out of one of those Old Earth serials Sulu loves so much
Spock to Artemis away team. Weve been following the situation from here.
With Tomalaks defeat, weve been able to intercept Romulan transmissions indicating where the Gorn are holding Captain Kirk.
I will send you the coordinates. It is imperative we reach the Captain before it is too late.
I have found a piece of Romulan technology. It seems to be the source of the transmissions.
I might be able to access it and replay more of their communications.
Im picking up Gorn life-signs over that ridge. They might lead us to Jim.
Were through. Itll take a few minutes to route the data stream to my PADD.
More Gorn just over there. We should try to ambush them.
An excellent tactical decision. For a doctor.
Thank you. I think.
I'm picking up a Romulan transmission originating nearby
It must be the unit escorting Captain Kirk

... proceed to the designated location. We look forward to meeting with your ambassador in person.
Be wary of pests that may interfere with our meeting. Tomalak out.
That is Tomalak, a Romulan Commander. My Enterprise has had several encounters with him.
He is duplicitous, and will stop at nothing to meet his goal.
Commander Tomalak, the meeting with the Gorn delegates commences as planned.
Are we really forging an alliance with these brutes?
My dear sub-commander, you shouldnt be unkind to our hosts.
After all, they will be on the front line when we expand into Federation space.
Brilliant, Commander. What of the Federation spies weve detected?
Dispose of them quietly. They must not interfere with our meeting.
Just ahead Keep your voices down. There's something happening.
Something is right. I see Romulans AND Gorn.
...weve made good on our promise to deliver Kirk. Now... Do we have your support?
<The Nest Father appreciates your gift as he approaches the great shedding.>
Its using a translator device. Im surprised the Gorn have a tool meant for diplomacy.
<The One known as Kirk is on his way to the Nest Father's base. But...>
<Before we speak further I assume the Federation troops stalking behind those rocks aren't your allies>
My apologies. We will see to this intrusion.
So the Gorn brought you here as well? Youll hand over your equipment, or well take it from you.
Were hardly prisoners. Were here for my friend!
First one to bring down the Klingon gets his bat'leth!
These are the Gorn I gave the slip. Cunning devils. Lets take them by surprise!
What, no makeshift dynamite this time?
Enterprise to Captain Kirk. I am glad to see you are well, Captain.
Spock! Its good to hear your voice. But were not leaving yet. The Gorn and Romulans are planning something.
Captain, we must regroup before they enact their plan. We must be prepared when they make their move.
What on earth happened to them?
It's Jim! Jim happened to them.
We should scan the area to see which way he went.
One of the Gorn is still alive. Perhaps he will have knowledge of Captain Kirk.
Im no herpetologist, Mr. Worf, but maybe theres something I can do for him.
I've found signs that he was here barely an hour ago.
We should follow this path!
Well, its minor miracle. Looks like hell pull through.
Hes pointing east! That might be the direction the Captain escaped to.
Give me a moment. We're running low on supplies.
Captain Kirk must be nearby. But among these rocks... it's like finding a needle in the proverbial haystack.
Can you try tracking his communicator? He might have managed to hide it when he was captured.
It's working! He's close!

Bones! Ive never been happier to see you!

Commander Burnham of the U.S.S. Discovery. Its a pleasure, Captain.

An Enterprise from the future, Jim. Wherever we ended up has scrambled the timeline.

Well, he sure looks like the real deal. Worf, what do you say? Tell me thats Jim over there!

Those are Romulans ahead. They must be part of the delegation.
Lets end this alliance before it gets started!
Keep pushing! We must be close to the center of the base.

<And you... my oldest, finest adversary.>

You think I cheated you. Unfairly robbed you of your prestige

<You have defeated me once more>

Bones? Thoughts?

As a xeno-anthropologist, I think I might have an idea

Im impressed, Burnham!
I wasnt sure it would work, but some species are more susceptible to flattery than others.
Ive scanned the area and found another route into the base.
Hold up, I think I hear voices coming from inside there!
You're right. And they sound human! More prisoners, maybe?
The door is locked. We must get inside!
Im reading life signs, but through this shielding I cant be sure if theyre allies or enemies...

Thank you! We were captured while on a mission to find dilithium deposits
We accidentally wandered too close to Gorn space, and they didnt take kindly to the intrusion.
Kirk to Enterprise. Spock, weve freed captured Starfleet officers. Two to beam up.

I wasn't sure at first, until they referred to me as his greatest adversary...

Its the only Gorn Ive ever met. As Spock would say, its

Well, we didnt part on the best of terms

The empire has changed a great deal since your time, Captain Kirk.

<Your empty threats betray your cowardice. You are unworthy of an alliance.>

You have one Romulan hour. I look forward to your surrender.

Romulans are beaming down. Well have to deal with them first!
Kill them all! A bar of latinum to the first trooper to bring one of them down.

With any luck, I can resequence the gene therapy involved so it might work for your species!

One device might be an outlier, but two? Theres something at work here. We need to beam back to the Artemis and study them properly!
I hear something down that corridor. Sounds like more headed this way!
Here is where we should make our stand! There is enough debris that we could construct a barricade.
Or we can force these bulkhead doors closed to buy some time!
Hurry! Theres almost on us!
Hrgghhhhh...
Well done, Worf. Remind me not arm-wrestle you later.
Call me crazy, but there must be a better place for a last stand.
You're right, Doctor. We should retreat.
Wait, this one's still breathing!
<Ah, Human-ally-of-Kirk. It looks like my fighting days are over.>

Im learning Gorn anatomy on the fly, but Ill give it a shot

Hell have quite a migraine in that massive skull, but he should be able to fight.

They must have beamed it in when the attack began.
Its transmitting our location to the warbird in orbit. We need to disable it!
We just need to figure out a way to turn this off. Is there a button or...?
Just shoot the thing and let's keep moving!
That works.
Perhaps we might be able to use this to our advantage. If we can adjust the transmission code

The Artemis is detecting weapons powering up on the Romulan Warbird in orbit!
Kirk to Enterprise. Spock, why dont we give our new friends on the Artemis, is it?... a helping hand.

I suggest the Artemis away team head to the nearest transporter pad while we engage the Romulans.

What do you mean Im not rea--

From the artifact?

Starfleet scum! You thought you could kidnap the great Gul Dukat?

It is pointless to reason with Cardassians, Burnham.
Youll pay for this treachery with your lives!
Hu'tegh! This atmosphere burns hotter than the fire caverns of Boreth!
Ill take your word for it. The ships picking up a long-range mayday transmission Federation by the sound of it.
Look over there, towards those hills Theres some sort of device half-buried in the sand. Could it be coming from that?
No, but scans show massive amounts of energy contained inside that thing; enough to knock a starship out of orbit!
Should we investigate?
We should find the mayday signal first. Could be injured survivors.

Hmmm There are several sets of footprints here, most likely Cardassian. A large group passing right through the dune.
Theyre heading straight for the mayday signal.
Theres a smaller set of footprints heading off to the side, around the dune. It might be a shortcut!
We should press on. If the Cardassians reach the signal source before we do, any survivors will suffer a gruesome fate.
If that side trail means we can beat the Cardassians to the beacon, its a risk worth taking.
Ahead of us! A crashed Starfleet shuttle!
Thats the source of the mayday.
Hurry, lets look for survivors!
Federation fools! Cease your pursuit of Gul Dukat! You have no authority here!
Ah! *growls*Now the Cardassian presence here makes sense. They're attempting to rescue their Commander!
Will your kind never learn?! I will not be caged!
Stand down, Dukat! We have you outnumbered.
You think I face you alone? The gods are on my side.
Odo was a fool to think this is some mere trinket.
This is a BLACK DURANJA: a vessel fashioned to contain the power of the PAH WRAITHS!
AGGHHHHHHHHH!
Are you all alright?
Worst headache Ive ever had but Im alive.
I felt like I was fighting against something truly evil.
On Vulcan we were taught that evil, as most races define the word, is merely a failure of reason.
But that thing might be the exception to the rule.
Scans aren't picking up any traces of that entity on Dukat.
It probably abandoned its host in search of another. I doubt itll find one on this desolate planet.
Let us hope you are correct.
McCoy to Artemis. Three to beam up with one Cardassian in tow.
I dont recognize this shuttle type
It is a runabout from Deep Space Nine, Doctor, after your time.
Nobodys here, but the debris fields stretches over the dunes.
Follow the debris. We might find survivors.
According to this data recorder, the runabout was shot down when approaching the planet.
That could have been the work of the strange device we found.
The runabout is abandoned, but it seems to have been used as a prisoner transport.
The crash must have disabled the holding cells force field.
I found footprints leading away from the shuttle Let's follow them.
The data from the ships computer says the pilot was somebody named Odo?
Odo is an old colleague of mine. A Changeling in charge of security on Deep Space Nine.
The manifest says he was transporting a prisoner named Gul Dukat to Bajor to stand trial.
Gul Dukat! One of the worst wretches the Federation has ever dealt with.
We must recapture him immediately!
Looks like some kind of a starship graveyard!
Judging by the damage, they were all downed by the same weapon that struck the shuttle.
The footprints lead directly through it.
Looks like a dust storms closing in. Better hurry, or well be breathing sand!
If these footprints are indeed Dukats, he seems to have gone deep into the desert.
We should follow before the storm erases the tracks.
Over there! That looks like a piece of a tracking cuff. Speaking from experience
He must have tried to knock it off. We can use this piece to track him.
Theres some form of encampment by those rocks.
Looks like a makeshift shelter, maybe Dukats?
This blasted sand covered his tracks!
Lets investigate. There may still be something there we can use to find him.
I cant see anything in this storm!
If we stop now, Dukats home free!
Over here! Its a datapad. Looks like Dukat plans to rendezvous with a Cardassian vessel and escape.
Were in luck. Had it not been for the storm, he would have escaped already.
For a Klingon, you sure know how to look on the bright side.
If we press on, we can catch Dukat before he escapes.
Dukat left equipment behind in his shelter.
Looks like medical supplies. I can put these to good use.
Just when I was glad to be rid of the Cardassians

Our own! Any treasure buried in these sands is ours!

You congratulate yourselves too soon!

He would have first sought shelter from the storms.
Well, I can't match Vulcans when it comes to logic, but
the shuttle crashed in a valley with only two obvious exits. We know Dukat went one way. My best guess is Odo went the other.
Tread carefully. There might be more mercenaries nearby.
Lets get as high as we can. Well have a better chance of spotting him.
Your tactical acumen is impressive, Doctor.
Not tactics, Worf. Just plain common sense!
Over there! The mercenaries camp!
The area must be teeming with them.
We should avoid them. Were here for a rescue, not a war.
You are right. We should avoid unnecessary combat.
Look there! Is that a combadge in the sand?
Yes! This belongs to Odo. The Bajoran design is distinctive. We're on the right track.
If left alone they might ambush us at any point. Best to deal with them now!
They might know where Odo is!
Id say thats a door built to keep people out. Or to keep something in.
Yes, and its architecture and patterns are similar to those other devices weve come across.
It seems to be shut tight. I dont see a way Odo could have gotten inside.
Odos form is somewhat... fluid. Hes able to change it in order to get through tight spaces.
Sounds like Starfleets now recruiting all kinds of interesting folks.
Well, if nobodys got the key, how do we open this thing?
Perhaps we can use our tricorders to locate the locking mechanism and disrupt it?
It might be possible to destroy the rock around the door with our phasers, so that we might pass through.
Interesting! Scans show there's an immense structure hidden behind it.
Faint traces of energy, most likely to power the locking mechanism.
I think I can override the lock
Stop! It's another one of the alien devices.
This one is more active than the other. Scans reveal heavier shielding, and energy pulsing out across nearby rocks.
We should steer clear of it. Finding Odo is our priority.
Lets look for a path around it.
Resist...
...futile...
Ahead of us  a Borg drone!
A Borg? Like a cyborg?

Exizztenz...
...iz -  iz -  izzz over
Well, when you put it that way
Odd. This Borg drone seemed far less functional than others I've encountered.
Who knows how long its been trapped in here?
Yes, it has fallen into disrepair. Although these walls do resemble the interior of the species ships.
The complex is silent. Only a few of the mechanisms here seem to be working properly, if powered at all.
Lets find Odo before hes  what did you call it? Assimilated?
Up ahead! Are those Starfleet crew?
What are the odds that Starfleet officers are just hanging around an abandoned alien facility?
Look at their eyes! Ive not known eyes that glow like that.
Theyve spotted us. And they dont look friendly!
They dissolve when defeated!
Changelings like Odo?
Similar, but no. Perhaps they are part of a Borg experiment
Over there! That door must be important. It's heavily guarded.
We are...the B-B-Borg.
You will be...
....be... assimilated.
RESISTANCE IS
FUTILE!
Careful! There's some sort of flooding here.
Scans show high amounts of dimethyl cadmium, hexavalent chromium and a mix of other toxic ingredients.
Not a cocktail you want to drink.
Time is short. We can simply wade across.
I can give you a hypospray to prepare you, but dont blame me for the hangover.
Ugh... I feel nauseous
It will pass
Ive had moonshine that hit harder.
Lets look for another way around.
Perhaps in this case, as the human Shakespeare once said, "discretion is the better part of valor".
Borg! Hundreds of them!
They seem... dormant?
It could be that they all shut down when the lights went out in here.
Let's investigate.
Bear with me... The circuitry here is very corroded.
The last entry was almost 200 years ago. Strange to think this was around even before my time.
The data is badly corrupted. There's a reference to some sort of atmospheric disaster.
Perhaps meteorites have damaged this facility. That would explain the craters on the surface.
The facility seems to have come back online in response to an intruder.
That could be Odo. He could be in here somewhere.
Quiet now. No sense waking the locals
Odo!! Can you hear us?

Do you hear that humming? I think its powering up!

Easier said than done. Its heavily shielded.

Ready phasers!
Just give me a moment, I think I can override it

They are definitely not Borg. Almost closer to Changelings
Lets hope they didnt do something to Odo!
More of the doppelgangers!
Odo, any idea what these things are?

I've seen them coming and going since I was captured. All from deeper inside the Complex.
Primary Objective: Protect pool from intruders.
Secondary protocol: Assimilation.

Somethings emerging from the pool!
It looks like Odo?
But I never came into contact with the fluid.
Well, it doesnt look like it wants a friendly chat.
Defend yourselves!
Sorry, my friend, but one of me is all this universe can handle.
And Ive got the Nexus device.
I think one of the Borg called it a Reactor

No. We're just... navigating cautiously.
All of these passages look the same to me. Left turn maybe? It seems quieter. Darker and creepier. But quieter.
Hmmm... The lights seem to be working along the corridor on the right.
More power will likely mean more Borg. Stay alert!

But it was an error! They have admitted as much.
Although my values align with the Federations, I still feel my blood boiling over this transgression in instinct.
I understand the logic, of course, but that should give you an understanding of how severe this is for a Klingon.
In your time, Michael, our species went to war because of the relic. Is it any wonder the Klingons fight so fiercely to punish the crew? They will not relent.
I'm picking up hundreds more bio-readings converging on our position. We need to retreat!
Huh. I thought you'd be arguing for us to stay and fight.
As Kahless himself once said, "The wind does not respect a fool."
Were close.
I'm detecting a mass of Klingon bio-signatures ahead.
They must have been put in our way to guard the Reactor Im detecting.
Hu'tegh! And they're not alone. One of them is wearing the ceremonial armor of the Torchbearer.
The Klingon champion who defends the Beacon of Kahless! I had a run in with one.
And youre sure you cant just access the Reactor from here?
Hmph. Didnt think so.
Were right over the source of the signal. I can use my tricorder in conjunction with our Reactors to access it.
The device powering the reality were in definitely isnt of the magnitude of the Reactors powering the Spheres. Which is good news!
So, any ideas as to how to reprogram this scenario so its winnable?
I dont think we need to win it. Our goal has always been to find the portal. Yes, it had previously appeared when we won, but in this case why dont we just make it appear?
Brilliant, Michael!
One portal coming up!
There! Injured crew members ahead of us!
I'll... hang back and let you deal with this. A Klingon showing up might escalate things
Were here to help! Are you all right?
I... yes. Barely. Who are you? I don't recognize your uniforms.
We're from the U.S.S. Artemis. What had happened here?
You're a welcome sight, were in dire straits.
Our route took us close to the Beacon of Kahless.
The Beacon is a holy relic of the Klingon empire. What were you thinking approaching it?
It was a mistake! We had no idea what the thing was... but theyre accusing us of aggression and attempting to defile their sacred vessel.
They announced that everyone on board in sentenced to death!
Well, we can't have that.
We need to get these people to safety. Can you get them ready to move, Doctor?
I'll try. Cover me while I patch them up!
There are Klingons converging on this spot!
So, we drive them back. Then we can deal with the wounded.
Ive locked on a reading akin to the Reactors. Its definitely not as considerable, so perhaps this reality isnt as major as an actual Sphere.
Lets give your Reactor theory a spin! Do you think you can reprogram this door away?
Yes! I can use my tricorder in conjunction with our Reactors
Im accessing the underlining structure of this reality. Its complex, but give me a few moments.
The door disappeared!
Incredible.
I need to be closer to the signal source to do anything showier than that, though.
We should not waste any time or potential Reactor power.
Mr. Worf, you are a fine warrior and loyal ally. But you, Sir, are no fun.
Intriguing! We appear to be on a Federation vessel. Scans showing damage throughout several decks.
An attack?
I'm receiving several jumbled messages. It appears Klingons have boarded the ship and taken control of key areas.
Ive learned its generally safer when Klingons keep their hands off Starfleet ships!
Present company excluded.
Hmph.
And that is the nature of your test.
Jim?! Wait... you're the Caretaker.
This test echoes the values your friend possesses in abundance.
Recklessness? Willingness to drag us all into some fool adventure?
The test of Cunning lies before you. You have shown a willingness to believe in your goal and to persevere through all odds.
But some obstacles cannot be beaten head on.
Find the portal and the end of this trial.
And he's gone. Helpful as ever.
This seems impossible. Its a regular its the Kobayashi Maru!
The academy test?
Exactly. I assume you've both taken it?
I have. And, like every other cadet, failed it every time. I was furious when I found out it was a no-win scenario.
Either you rescue the crew and cause a war with the Klingon empire or abandon them to die.
This scenario, too, is designed for failure. My people wont relent here. We wont survive their onslaught, and if we leave, these people will perish
But here's the thing: in my time, Captain Kirk DID beat the Kobayashi Maru test. In good ol Jim fashion, he got creative: he snuck in before the test and reprogrammed the computer.
So we should take a page out of Captain Kirks book and cheat.
But how? Theres no computer we have access to
This reality likely works like the other Spheres. Theres a Reactor or a similar device running it. We find it and change its programming.
But were not Engineers yet. Were unable to affect the Nexus technology!
Im done waiting for authorization from a hologram. All of us have dealt with unknown, ultra-advanced alien technology before. It is par for the course!
Im tuning my tricorder to the Reactors already in our possession. Lets find whatever is controlling the Caretakers little trial.
And here you are at last, through a combination of faith, determination and
Yes yes, we know: cunning. Way ahead of you, Confucius.
Correct, you have circumvented the directed path and have tapped into the Nexus itself. Although you will find that the more major constructs of it are not as easy to tamper with.
And now, there only remains...
No! No more trials! We have proven our abilities, and there is no time.
Regardless of your perception of readiness, the trials for an aspiring Engineer are a binary requirement. They must all be complete before you are able to engage the Reality Engine.
Federation!
We mean you no harm, were from the U.S.S. Art--
Apprehend them! Tomalak and Sela will have our hides if we let them reach the beacon!
Doesnt seem like these Romulans are open to dialogue and reason
I wish we could have resolved that differently.
She seemed certain the Federation is working against the Romulans.
Perhaps catching up to her commander will give more insight.
They certainly seem sure we're spying on them!
Hes subdued.
I'm not sure stunning him is what the test was about...
He did say at times you must show the other side the strength of your convictions!
Well... I don't see a sign we failed, so I supposed you're right.
Stop right there.
We're not here to fight.
You're a Klingon. Of course you're here to fight.
Fella has a point.
Hmph.
We are here to open a dialogue.
Bah! You are here to sabotage the beacon. You are too late in any case, Tomalak already departed with the data.
Stand down. Let us walk away and we'll do the same.
We wouldnt waste precious breath on you. The data we obtained will expose the Federation as the treacherous snakes you are! (they beam out)
Wait. Did a Romulan just call us treacherous snakes? That's one for the books.
We're not looking for trouble.
And yet youre here, and youve found it!
More Romulans. And another sensor beacon.
Federation. How... unsurprising. Come here to hide traces of your treachery?
I have no idea what you're talking about.
You claim to know nothing about the Federation ships that have been regularly slipping across the neutral zone and spying on my people?
We have hard evidence of your kind breaking countless treaties.
Let us review the evidence and attempt to make sense of this. Would you rather try than start an all-out war?
I wont deny youre making sense. I will allow you to meet with my commanding officer.
I doubt you'll be able to convince him, though. He's dealt with your kind before.
Do you take us for fools? We have evidence of Federation ships slipping across the neutral zone and spying on our people.
That is against Federation values. Lay down your weapons now, or we will force them out of your hands!
It looks like the Romulan commander is ahead of us, ready to depart.
We need to stop him before he does!
There must be a way we can reach an agreement here!
I will not fall for whatever ruse you are concocting.
Our sensor beacon has evidence that elements within Section 31 have been spying on my people for over a decade.
As a loyal servant of the empire, it's my duty to report this violation to the High Council!
As much as it pains me to admit... you might be right. Section 31 has never been the most trustworthy of organizations.
You you admit this? Hmmm, Ill listen. What do you propose?
Give us a copy of your data. We'll report it to Starfleet. If it's true, they'll investigate further and reply along proper diplomatic channels.
You realize your copy could be altered.
As could yours. We're asking you to trust we'll deal with any potential breach of diplomacy.
Very well. But I will not stay to converse any further. Take the data.
Halt. We can't let you leave with Federation intel.
Oh? You think you can stop me?
Our sensor beacon has evidence that elements within Section 31 have been spying on my people for over a decade.
Its my duty to report this violation to the High Council!
And you're not going to listen to reason, are you?
Reason from your kind? Hardly. You are treacherous scum. Romulans have learned the Federation can't be trusted.
Thats rich coming from you! If you won't listen to reason, you'll listen to a phaser!
You stand on the precipice of the final trial.
And you appear as my former captain, Jean-Luc Picard.
He seemed appropriate for this test.

Aside from belief, will and cunning, it was determined an Engineer requires another trait: the rare ability to unify the multitudes of minds required in such an epic endeavor as the creating of the Nexus.
This was often done through dialogue and reason, but at times one must bend opposition in the name of the greater good.
Find the portal to complete your trial.
Ahead of us! It's the last portal!
Congratulations, crew of the Artemis.
You have persevered through trial after trial; shown traits that allowed the original Engineers to build this wonder we stand in.
You truly are worthy of mantle as Engineers.
Are you seeing this? My tricorder is showing a flow of information pouring down into the Artemis' datacore.
Diagrams, schematics...
You will use this to help repair the Reality Engine.
But first, you must purge it of the Dreamless presence.
The Engine seems darker now, doesn't it?
The Caretaker did say its badly damaged.
Who knows how long weve been engaged in the Caretakers trials...
Long enough for the Dreamless to take over!
You have no hope of preventing us from toppling this machine.
Well see about that!
We cannot allow you to go any further.
You must let us past. The lives of millions are at stake!
We understand your concern. We are trying to save them as well.
You are taking their fate into your own hands. Youre assuming a moral high ground where you have no right to do so.
We are bringing order back to our people and the universe. Everything ends.
Thats it - the core!
And that must be the leader of the Dreamless.
The intruders Relentless in your quest to stop us.
I saw a glimpse of who you once were. Before you ended up here.
You were a scholar, a parent. Surely, its not in your nature to commit murder of this scale!
You think what we are doing is murder? All life must end at one point. All life!
Enough! You are fools to protect this place! It is a prison. An affront to the natural flow of the universe!
Maybe. The Nexus might be nothing more a misguided and hubristic creation of an ancient civilization, ensnaring anyone caught within it.
But all those mind and souls exist here now, and youre not the arbiter who will decide they must cease.
So righteous and full of determination.
Do you really think the Nexus was created out of pure benevolence? You would be delusional to believe so.
We have done what we set out to do here today. My consciousness now exists inside the network flowing through the Nexus just as much as it does out here.
You may stabilize this Reality Engine, but it is only one in a sea of them, and they will soon be extinguished. (She beams out)
I hate to say it but... what DO we know about the Nexus? Have we done the right thing?
I know that we wont let someone just flip the switch on all these lives. (they beam out back to the Artemis)
She has retreated from this Engine, but melding with its core has revealed a secret to her  one we had hoped to hide away from the Dreamless
We have given you access to their next target. Please honor your duty as Engineers and make haste, before all is lost.
This console can direct the platform to one of the two exits.
So... we're stumbling blindly forward, huh?
What is it you told us Captain Kirk would say? To boldly go?
Still, I think he at least had some idea which direction he was heading in.
Let's take the left-hand path.
Any particular reason?
Left is my throwing arm.
Good enough for me!
We've been lucky so far, so Im fine with either.
Fine. Thousands of years of evolution, crewing one of the most advanced vessels ever created, and we're relying on luck to save millions of lives.
So sure, I vote for the right-hand path. Why not.
You stand at the threshold of the Engines core.
We began this journey with little idea of the Nexus or its nature.
Weve come together as a crew, united despite being from different cultures, backgrounds and timelines!
I cant think of anyone Id rather have by my side at this moment!
Now you got this old man all teary-eyed! Lets get in there and put a stop to this!
The great Kahless once said, The enemy may be so strong none can stand against them.
Yet we must, for I would rather die than know we failed to stand as warriors when it mattered.
Today we honor those words! Together we shall conquer all obstacles!
Well said, my friend!
You would have made quite a name for yourself coaching football back at the academy, Mr. Worf!
As much as Id like to get this over and done with so I can get back to sickbay where I belong...
Strikes me as madness to just run in there halfcocked!
Lets at least scan the place first  and see what were dealing with!
Sensible as ever, my friend!
And that preparation might give us the edge we need!
Welcome, Engineers.
Oh, so we got the shiny title! What now?
As we speak, the Dreamless have penetrated most of the Reality Engines defenses.
Information required to repair the Engine has been uploaded to your ship and can be accessed via the Reactors.
Take them to the Engine's core to stabilize it and bring the systems back online.
The self-proclaimed Dreamless are zealots and will risk everything to stop you.
The damage is extensive. Were running out of time!
We estimate catastrophic failure in less than 5 Terran minutes.
At present, the primary Dreamless has nearly finished merging her consciousness into the Engine.
That sounds undesirable.
This Engines protocols are designed to prevent unauthorized access, but the Dreamless have been sabotaging the system and gathering its Reactors for a long time.
If their leader is able to merge her consciousness with this Engine, shell be able to shut it down, and it wont be long until she can extend her power to the rest of the Nexus.
There must be something we can do to prevent that from happening!
As an Engineer you can merge your consciousness into the Engine much the same way.
Though, such a feat requires tremendous mental prowess.
Michael, you are one of the most powerful people Ive had the pleasure of standing beside!
Not to mention youre the adopted sister of the best mindmelder Ive ever known. Well, the only one.
Michael, I believe in you.
I... Ill try.
I Its working. I can feel the walls spreading out around me like my mothers arms. Everything is golden. Everything is so large. I had no idea.
I can feel someone else here. Huge. Taller than a mountain before me. Shes so righteous. So angry. Her children, her mates - all gone. All dead so long ago.
Shes noticed me! Im trying to evade her. I think shes losing focus on the Engine shes pursuing me.
She ejected me out of the system! I could feel her exerting energy to do it it may have slowed her down
You will not be able to access the Engine again from here. You must arrive at its core.
We must warn you that the process is almost complete. You have virtually run out of time.
No! Let me try to access the Engine again using the Reactor.
Are you sure? The last time your bio-readings were off the charts. If you do it again...
Then Ill have the best doctor in Starfleet looking after me, wont I?
Well, just get on with it then!
Im back in.
I can feel her all around us!
Her grief is everywhere. Shes so alone. Everyone she has known is long gone.
She misses each of them. Her existence is a solitary one. Her entire world is lost!
The great library she founded, the crimson seas she swam in as a child - all gone. Her sadness is overwhelming! I cant... agghhhhh!!!
Doctor! Get her out of there! Its killing her!
Im all right. I have never felt pain like hers before.
It bubbled inside her, and broke through the reality of the Sphere she was in. It could no longer contain her mind and soul. Thats the genesis of all these Dreamless. And now theyre here.
No wonder they view the Nexus as they do.
But we cant let them make the decision for all the others and continue this destruction.
Did she notice you again?
Your friends actions have slowed the process by 78.9 earth minutes.
We still have time!
The Nexus has returned.
But you are not alone...
An unstoppable energy wave that threatens all life in the galaxy.
After its appearance in the year 2371, Federation scientists developed technology to harness the energy...
After its first appearance years ago, Federation scientists developed technology to harness the energy...
...and built a starship able to enter the Nexus and rescue those trapped inside.
This is the U.S.S. ARTEMIS..
The U.S.S. Artemis.
YOU are its captain.
As you enter the Nexus, it is not the utopian dreamscape survivors have described...
Previous survivors of the Nexus have described a dimension of idealized dreamscapes
...but a nightmare.
Once inside the Nexus, you watch helplessly as your crew disappear one by one!
And you are left to face a deadly enemy.
Facing off with a Cardassian warship, you are hailed by a HUMAN voice aboard the vessel...
Scanning the strange ether within the <color=#fff15c>Nexus,</color> you detect a life sign that matches Starfleet records...
...only to encounter an unexpected visitor.

Dammit, Jim, Im a doctor, not a --
Hey! Where in tarnation am I?
Welcome aboard the U. S. S. Artemis.
A Klingon?! In Starfleet?!
That reaction is becoming tiresome.

What trap is this? I was returning from a visit to QonoS when my shuttle was struck, and now--
Wait. This appears to be a Starfleet vessel, albeit one I do not know...
Federation vessel, lower your shields and prepare to be boarded!
It appears my arrival was timely. Send me over to their ship and I will silence these Cardassian cowards!
Theres no time to waste. You send him to help Burnham on the Cardassian vessel.

After a successful leap into the Nexus, the U.S.S. Artemis comes under fire from an unknown enemy.
Before Commander Burnham can leave the unknown vessel, its warp core must be disabled.
The U.S.S. Artemis responds to a distress signal from an unknown Federation base.
With no reply from survivors within Federation Base, the away team must investigate the facility with caution.
Project TALOS' defenses have run amok, complicating the search for survivors within the base.
The computer core of Talos must be disabled at all costs, to prevent further loss of life.
The U.S.S Artemis recieves a message from Starfleet - Captain Kirk has vanished.
The hunt for Kirk brings the away team into conflict with Romulan mercenaries.
The team uncover evidence of a far reaching plot to create an alliance between the Romulans and the Gorn.
On the Gorn homeworld, the away team finds clues that point them to where Kirk is being held.
The away team and Kirk come face to face with one of his oldest foes, the Gorn Commander.
Enraged, Tomalak and the Romulans attack. Only by working togther can Kirk and the Gorn prevail.
A mysterious signal reaches the U.S.S Artemis from the surface of a desert planet.
In the ruins of a prison transport, the away team find that Gul Dukat has escaped capitivity.
Prisoner secure, the away team hunt for the shuttle's pilot - Odo.
Odo's trail leads into a ruined Borg outpost, buried deep beneath the shifting sands.
In the heart of the Borg outpost the team encounters a mimetic pool, capable of imitating any lifeform.
Alarms sound as the Borg awaken. It's up to the away team to destroy the outpost's power and escape.
A call for help leads to a colony suffering from a mysterious disease.
Battling against maddened inhabitants, the away team makes its way to Dr Beverly Crusher's clinic.
The infection has claimed Dr. Crusher as a victim. The away team must neutralize her and restore order.
Clues to the disease point towards a Klingon research facility; this outbreak might not be natural.
Cure in hand, the away team return to the colony and attempt to distribute it.
The neural parasites have been dealt with - now only the mastermind behind the attack remains: Khan.
Tensions are risng between the Federation and the Klingon Empire in the Neutral Zone.
A Klingon Bird-of-Prey has been shot down by a mysterious attacker.
Borg drones are attacking the planet and plan to re-assimilate Seven of Nine.
The away team needs tor prevent the Cube from contacting the Collective for more reinforcements.
The Borg are retreating back into a Transwarp conduit and attempting to physically contact the Collective.
Something or someone is still controling the Borg and needs to be stopped.
The U.S.S. Artemis finds a lone Starfleet vessel, the U.S.S. Pioneer, adrift and unresponsive.
The U.S.S. Pioneer's crew have succumbed to a form of madness that renders them confused and highly aggressive.
Long-ranged scans have revealed a badly damaged Warbird tumbling through space: the I.K.S. Ning'Tao.
Above the planet floats the Cardassian ship Martok warned you about. The Kornaire.
Beaming down to the surface of the planet to find the source of this madness.
To boldly go where no one has gone before.
The U.S.S. Artemis is floating outside the enormous Reality Engine built around a captured star.
To earn the Caretaker's help, the away team much complete four tests, the first being the Test of Faith.
The second test is the Test of Will, pitting the away team against the Borg once more.
Faith and Will may not always be enough, the away team faces the Test of Cunning.
The final test is the Test of Reason, to prove that some conflicts can be settled through dialogue and tact.
Earning the mantle of Engineers, the away team must stop the Dreamless and repair the Reality Engine.

The away team passes by, avoiding a potentially dangerous encounter.

The away team retreats deeper into the base, searching for a better position to defend themselves.
The away team continues on, unable to save the Gorn.

The away team has gathered resources from the surrounding area.
