The away team is able to override the device, sending the Romulans into disarray, lowering their Defense.
The away team has gathered resources from the surrounding area.
A trail leads away from the device. Perhaps once used by those who built it. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
The away team successfully hacked the strange device, disabling it. Feeling hopeful, the team receives a Morale Boost.
The away team follows the large group of footprints. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
Exploring the narrow path reveals a shortcut through the rocks. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
The away team follows the debris, revealing a small, sheltered trail. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
Signs of a scuffle lead the team to believe that the assailant went east. The away team collects supplies left behind then pushes forward.
Scanning the ship's logs has revealed that the pilot was Odo, who is nowhere to be found. The away team advances on high alert, receiving a Defense Bonus.
A smoldering firepit and footprints reveal that Dukat is close. The away team advances down an alternate path on high alert, receiving a Defense Bonus.
A tracking cuff confirms that Dukat is close. The away team pushes down an alternate path in pursue of him.
As the storm worsens, the away team quickly pursues footprints leading away from the campsite. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
With Dukat's position and plans to escape revealed, the away team gains an advantage. Feeling hopeful, the Team receives a Morale Boost.
The away team successfully salvages some medical supplies from the shelter.
The away team pushes forward into the canyon, revealing a clearing ahead. The away team has unlocked an alternate path.
The away team pushes forward up a narrow gap in the rocks. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
The away team pulls back, avoiding an encounter with Klingon Bandits. While retreating, a combadge buried in the sand reveals Odo was here. The away team pushes forward in their pursuit.
The away team ambushes nearby Klingon bandits! Gaining the tactical advantage, the away team receives a Speed Bonus.
The away team successfully hacked the strange device, disabling it. Feeling hopeful, the team receives a Morale Boost.
Using their phasers the away team is able to create a small gap in the rock around the door and squeeze inside.
Scans reveal a large, underground, structure teeming with energy. Prepared for combat, the away team pushes forward receiving an Attack Bonus.
The away team pushes forward through the waste, placing them deeper in the structure. Footprints trailing away from the waste indicate that the away team is not alone.
The away team pulls back in an attempt to avoid the hazardous waste spill. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
Examining the alcove reveals that the Borg have been dormant for hundreds of years, but why are they here? The away team proceeds with caution, receiving a Defense Bonus.
The away team cautiously advances forward in their pursuit of Odo. The away team proceeds with caution, receiving a Defense Bonus.
The away team quickly pushes forward in their pursuit of Odo. Feeling determined, the away team receives a Speed Bonus.
The Borg device is disabled from multiple phasers shots. With phasers in hand, the away team receives an Attack Bonus.
The Borg systems have detected the hacking intrusion and has alerted nearby Borg drones.
The away team pushes forward down the left corridor in search of Odo. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
The away team pushes forward down the right corridor in search of Odo. The away team has discovered an alternate path.
The away team disables the shield and frees Odo.
The away team overloads the shield with sustained fire from their phasers and frees Odo.
The away team fires their phasers collapsing the room onto the pool.
The away team gathers a sample of the fluid in the pool.
The away team establishes a link with the fluid. It's confused, frightened... and angry.
The away team charges towards the Borg, receiving an Attack Bonus.
Being severely outnumbered, the away team wisely chooses to find another route. The away team receives a Speed Bonus.
Rerouting the power to the shields, the away team receives a Defense Bonus.
The away team disrupts the Borg's local communication, slowing the reactions of the Borg drones.
The away team ruptures the chemcial pipe and the Borg as weakened as their wade through the corrosive chemicals.
The away team is able to partially sedate the organic components of the Borg, reducing the effectiveness of Borg attacks.
The stabilized officer indicates a path through the forest for the team to explore.
The away team continues on towards the Federation outpost.
The away team collects a small handful of resources.
The PADD reveals the position of nearby infected Starfleet officers.
Accessing the device has led the away team to a nearby group of Romulans, who may have information about the infection.
Phasers at the ready, the away team moves further towards the medical cache.
Most of the crates are empty, but a few still hold useful supplies.
Before falling unconscious, the medic gives the away team a hypospray containing a regenerative agent.
The away teams phasers make short work of the wreckage, opening the path forward.
The away team is able to override the doors security protocols and open a path forward.
The stabilized Starfleet engineer gives the away team a shield for upcoming battles.
The Neurazine has neutralized the infected outside, allowing the away team to avoid battle.
The away team opens the doors, allowing the infected inside. Theyre thrust into combat.
A quick injection of Cordrazine prepares the away team for battle, the away team receives an Attack Boost.
Without an obvious cure for Dr. Crusher, the away team heads out in search of Theragen to complete her research.
Dr. Crushers disease has been slowed, but not stopped. She may be able to give the away team valuable information.
The away team examines Dr. Crushers research into the disease, the away team receives a Morale Boost.
The away team slowly moves from crate to crate. Most are empty. One, marked Federation Prax X-345 supplies isn't.
The away team scans the warehouse and quickly finds the Theragen.
The away team decides against confrontation, looking for a safer way into the outpost.
The away team is prepared to risk combat to get the cure and get back to Dr. Crusher. The away team receives an Attack Boost.
A diplomatic approach has avoided combat with the guards.
The away teams search reveals notes on a modified form of Betatephlin, used as a carrier for a parasitic life form. This discovery will help create a cure.
The away team dashes out a nearby exit, leaving the lab before any guards can arrive. The away team receives a Speed Boost.
Using diplomacy, the away team convinced the scientist to give them the cure for the disease.
The away team expertly works the machines, quickly harvesting enough samples to synthesize a cure.
The away team prepares to fight the pursuing guards.
The away team activates the air filtration unit to start dispersing the cure throughout the outpost.
The stabilized Engineer is able to set up a defense grid for the away team. The away team receives a Defense Boost.
The away team rushes back to Dr. Crusher, even though the path is perilous.
The away team focuses on activating the filtration unit, only to be shocked as infected personnel emerge and surround them! It's a trap!
The away team warily scans the area and discovers life signs, an ambush! Reactly quickly, the away team prepares for battle. The away team receives a Speed Boost.
The away team searches the nearby storage containers for any additional supplies, interrupted by the sound of approaching infected.
The away team is able to bypass security protocols and hack into the defense network to open the doors. The away team receives a Defense Bonus.
The repeated firing of phasers against the door has attracted unwanted attention.
A quick search of the outpost's blueprints reveals an alternate entrance that should be unlocked.
The away team helps the officer to his feet, and he nods gratefully. He provides them with what few medical supplies he has and the codes to the door.
The away team decides not to waste any of the remaining cure. Better to save it for emergencies.
The filtration unit is activated, dispersing the cure throughout the area. Nearby infected are neutralized allowing the away team to avoid battle.
In such dangerous situations, it pays to use every resource available. Luckily there's a crate of those nearby.
The away team searches for an alternate path leading them around the noxious area. The away team discovers an <b>Alternate Path<b>.
The away team bravely plunge into the noxious cloud... and immediately regret their decision as their throats and eyes begin to burn. The away team suffers an <b>Attack Penalty<b>.
Heeding the advice of McCoy, the away team gives him a moment to prepare a counter-reagent to deal with the effects of the gas.
High tensions and a misunderstanding results in a sudden escalation towards violence.
Steady heads prevail and after some quick negotiations the Klingons sheath their weapons.
Aiming carefully, the away team's phasers cut through the dense foliage, carving a path through the forest. The away team discovers an <b>Alternate Path<b>.
Carefully the away team retraces their footsteps. The forest widens back out and soon they're able to find a new path forward.
Quickly, the away team spreads out around the clearing at key positions. When the mercenaries return, they'll be ready. The away team receives a <b>Defense Bonus<b>.

The away team begins to patch up the wounded Klingons. The mercenaries might attack at any moment, but the away team wont sacrifice Federation values in the face of fear. The away team receives a <b>Morale Bonus<b>.
The away team vanishes into the surrounding forest and stay silent, waiting for the mercenaries to blunder into their trap. The enemy team suffers a <b>Defense Penalty<b>.
The away team sets off into the forest to catch the mercenaries unprepared at their camp. The away team receives an <b>Attack Bonus<b>.
The away team hurries towards the Sphere but quickly stumbles into a cluster of drones.
Scans of the area reveal several Borg drones approaching, the away team prepares for battle. The away team receives a <b>Tech Bonus<b>.
The away team cautiously searches the surrounding area, and encounters a group of Borg drones heading towards them. The away team receives a <b>Defense Bonus<b>.
The last thing the away team needs is more enemies. It's time to deal with these mercenaries once and for all.
Surprisingly, the mercenaries take the away team's words to heart. Hands ease off phasers and one of them even offers to help fight the intruders.  The away team receives a <b>Morale Bonus<b>.
Normally the away team would stop them, but today seems to be their lucky day. The away team have a friend to save. The away team runs on and their shouts and jeers quickly fade behind them.
A moment later the hack works and the door slides open. The away team discovers an <b>Alternate Path<b>.
A few shots with the away team's phasers burn through the door's mechanisms. The away team is able to shoulder it aside and move on into the complex. The away team discovers an <b>Alternate Path<b>.
The away team turns and heads back, eyes peeled for a doorway or vent. There has to be another route into the complex and they need to find it
Tapping into the network, the away team learns of Cube's intent to rejoin the Collective.
The away team is able to tap into the remodulation network and effectively block the Borg from seeing them as intruders. It won't hold for long. The away team receives a <b>Defense Bonus<b>.

Tapping into the nearby circuitry the away team sets up a relay to bypass the current around the room. Moments later, the lights in the room flicker then go out. Everything around them is silent.  The away team discovers an <b>Alternate Path<b>.
Gripping their phasers tightly, the away team charges forward in hopes of gaining the upper hand.
The away team decides to leave the data distribution node alone and move on. The away team discovers an <b>Alternate Path<b>.
Phaser fire reduces the node to atoms, but a moment later, the blare of an alarm sounds through the complex.
The away team reprogram the node and move forward, ignored by a few Borg who march past, oblivious to their presence. The away team receives a Defense Bonus.
The nearby recharging stations are disabled, keeping the drones docked in them in stasis. The away team discovers an <b>Alternate Path<b>.
The phasers shudder in the away team's hands but after a moment the forcefield flickers and drops, freeing the prisoners. The away team receives a <b>Morale Bonus<b>.
The forcefield shuts down long enough for the prisoners to flood out of the chamber to safety before reactivating. The away team receives a <b>Morale Bonus<b>.
The away team manipulates the Cube into diverting power into a non-existent critical repair, and away from the forcefield. The away team receives a <b>Morale Bonus<b>.
The Borg network is growing resistant to the away team's intrusions. But the away team acquires a rudimentary layout of the Borg Cube. The away team discovers an Alternate Path.
Accessing the Borg network proves unsuccessful as the amount of information is too vast and the network becomes more resistant to the away team's interference.
The phaser blast strikes the shield to little effect. The energy wall seems to shift for a moment, then adapt. An alarm starts blaring...
The away team is able to disable the forcefield for a moment, but before any of the prisoners can escape, it reactivates. The Borg have obviously adapted. An alarm sounds

Charging forward, the away team barrels directly into the drones. Theyre thrown back, falling over one another.
The away team retreats towards the smaller group, hoping to break out before they can surround them. The away team receives a <b>Speed Bonus<b>.
The away team searches for another way to access the Transwarp drive. The away team discovers an <b>Alternate Path<b>.

Explore the Star Trek universe in the official team-based RPG. Take command of the U.S.S. Artemis and warp into the mysterious Nexus, where youll discover new worlds and recruit over 40 characters from the entire Star Trek franchise - the Original Series, The Next Generation, Deep Space Nine, Voyager, Enterprise, Discovery, and Picard. Your crews skills and ingenuity will prove critical through an epic adventure in the Nexus, where nothing is as it seems.
By playing Star Trek: Legends, you agree to our terms of service:

LEAD YOUR AWAY TEAM: Use strategy to pick the right team members from your collection for the task at hand. Choose from all your favorite characters from the Star Trek universeKirk, Picard, Burnham, Janeway, Data, and many more.

BE A MASTER TACTICIAN: Use the right tactics to defeat enemies and complete missions. Each legend has their own unique set of skills and abilities that can be upgraded. From Spocks Vulcan Nerve Pinch to Worfs deadly Batleth.
COMMAND THE BRIDGE: Assign crew to posts at the bridge of the U.S.S. Artemis. From there, theyll support the away team and can make the difference between mission success and failure.
GRAND NARRATIVE CAMPAIGN: Boldly go into the Nexus! Engage in an epic storyline for control of the Nexus and the fate of the universe.

STUNNING GRAPHICS: Explore beautifully rendered 3D worlds, fully realized and lovingly animated characters, and a dynamic graphics system that provides a console-level experience on your Apple device.

Captain, we need all the help we can get on the Bridge. We should assign our new officer to the <color=#fff15c>Medical position.</color>
Captain, the Artemis has been gathering Nexus Energy during our missions on the planet.
We have enough to locate and beam in another ally from the depths of the Nexus.
I've set the Transporter coordinates for the Federation base, captain.
Head to the <color=#fff15c>Mission Screen</color> when youre ready to beam down.
Captain, while you were briefing Dr. McCoy, we've received a distress call from a nearby planet. It appears to be from a Federation base?
It could be an illusion created by the Nexus. It would not be prudent to rush into danger unprepared.
We're Starfleet, man. We can't just leave these people to die if there's a chance to save them!
What are your orders, captain?
Your choice resulted in a Branched Path. You can replay missions to explore alternate paths for additional rewards!
Captain, we're ready to beam down to the distress call.
We should hurry. Scans indicate Cardassian weapon fire on the planet surface.
Looks like the Artemis is stocked with Bio-mimetic gels.
They provide an effective boost to the bodys natural immune system.
In the <color=#fff15c>CREW ROSTER</color> you can view the Crew youve found in the Nexus.
Collect items to upgrade your <color=#fff15c>Crew Members Level</color> and <color=#fff15c>Rank,</color> or <color=#fff15c>Protomatter</color> to upgrade <color=#fff15c>Skills.</color>
Welcome to the Artemis Bridge Stations. Here you can assign new Crew Members to stations on the Bridge.
New bridge positions will open as you <color=#fff15c>Level Up</color>. Each Crew Member can only be assigned to certain stations.
Each officer has a <color=#fff15c>unique bonus</color> when assigned to a Bridge Station.
Glad to be serve, Captain!
Each officer has a <color=#fff15c>unique bonus</color> when assigned to the Bridge. This Crew Member increases the away teams Tech state.
The <color=#fff15c>Timed Summon</color> uses energy gathered automatically over time to rescue new crewmembers from the Nexus.
We can't always be successful, but Starfleet never gives in.
Captain, I've made logs of <color=#fff15c>Starfleet Directives</color> to help us get back on our feet.
Why don't we try to level up our team?
<color=#fff15c>Starfleet Directives</color> guide you to strengthen your crew and prepare yourself for upcoming missions.
Burnham to the Artemis, requesting emergency beam-out!
We'll regroup on the bridge. Burnham out.
Were going to need all the help we can get for this, Captain. Lets bring our new crewmember along.
CARDASSIAN SHIP
I feel Incredible! Thank you, doctor!
Hold your horses. Im not a miracle worker. The Artemis supplies have run out.
Well need to keep our eyes open for more <color=#fff15c>Bio-mimetic gels.</color>
I'm getting a bad feeling about that Federation base.
We should apply more <color=#fff15c>Bio-mimetic Gels</color> before we head down there.
An excellent idea, Doctor. A warrior must always be prepared for battle!
Take this chance to <color=#fff15c>Enhance</color> your Crew before the next Mission. Return to the <color=#fff15c>Bridge</color> when youre ready to depart.
Doctor, its time I repaid the favor for your help with the bio-mimetic gels.
We've recovered unstable <color=#fff15c>Protomatter</color> after our encounter with the Cardassians.
We can use it to counteract any ill effects from being trapped in the Nexus!
Well, just hold on now - - unstable, you said?
Let's get this over with. I'm not used to being the patient.
I seem to be all in one piece. I guess you can teach an old dog new tricks after all!
Youd better bring me along. Who knows what kind of trouble youll get yourselves into down there?
Captain, we await your orders. How should we proceed?
Science officer reporting. Where can I be of assistance?

Back aboard the Artemis, the crew gathers around the alien device, studying its unusual design
It begins to hum softly, glimmering with light, generating raw energy that rapidly intensifies
As the smell of ozone fills the air, the energy suddenly bursts outwards!
Outside the Artemis, reality lurches and comes apart.
A rip in space opens in front of the Artemis, powered by the same golden energy coming from the artifact
Before the crew can react, the Artemis is pulled through!
The scan was right Something WAS coming.
As reality collapses around the away team and gold energy flood the room, a shape emerges from the light.
They hear a harsh mechanical language from the apparition, impossibly alien. What appears to be a limb points toward the artifact in their possession
The Gorn snarls. Kirk fires his phaser at the intruder. But everything dissolves around them
The away team finds themselves back on the bridge of the Artemis.
The Gorn homeworld is gone
On the main viewscreen is a desolate red planet. A Federation distress call flashes...
The Borg called the mysterious artifacts "Reactors".
Back on the Artemis the crew studies the Reactors bizarre alien construction.
Scans show layers of nano-circuitry beneath the outer shell, coursing with the mysterious energy.
There is no doubt about the power these constructs have over the Nexus and their impact on its reality and flow.
Could these Reactors be the building blocks of the Nexus?
And if they are, why are they creating the rifts pulling the Artemis from place to place?
Further investigation shows the devices arent generating power, but instead gathering it from somewhere deeper in the Nexus
The possibility of an intricate system powering the Nexus is fascinating to the crew, and is the very reason you were sent here as captain of the Artemis.
If more Reactors are found, it might be possible to triangulate the location of the energys source, and finally unlock the secrets of the Nexus!
But the danger is clear now. The Artemis isn't the only one in pursuit of the Reactors.
Whoever controlled Khan demanded possession of the artifact from the away team.
The voice, they agree, was alien. Worse still, it was flat, cold and utterly implacable.
Despite the threat, the Artemiss mission is clear: solve the mystery of the Nexus and rescue those trapped inside!
With the away team safely on board the Artemis, the bridge is flooded with light. On the main viewscreen, the Borg Cube erupts in a massive explosion!
Another challenge inside the Nexus has been conquered But mysteries remain
The newest Reactor joins the four previously recovered by the crew. They all light up, as if in response to the arrival of one of their own.
The data gleaned from the devices may allow the crew to map the Nexus. If they can only find one more
Impossibly, the back wall of the Bridge dissolves into a colorful fog.
The Dreamless glide towards the crew with ease, bending reality around them in a bid to claim the Reactors.
Over the shriek of bending metal and glass, you give the command to bring together the six Reactors!
The Artemis warps violently, and when it emerges on the other side, golden light floods its deck.
The crew gathers at the main viewscreen, staring in wonder at the alien world outside  the true Nexus Space.
Back inside the Sphere left behind by the Artemis, reality crumbles and dissolves.
The three Dreamless that attacked the ship float among the fragments, unconcerned by the devastation around them
In their ancient language, one of them says: Come. We must follow them to the Reality Engine.
